  "text": "The Rust compiler's trait method resolution and error reporting involves two main phases: candidate collection and ambiguity error reporting.\n\n## Candidate Collection\n\nThe primary file for collecting trait method candidates is `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs`. This module contains:\n\n1. **`assemble_candidates`** (line 27): The main entry point that examines all in-scope trait implementations (impls) and assembles a list of candidate implementations. It handles negative trait predicates differently from positive ones.\n\n2. **`assemble_candidates_from_impls`** (line 593): Searches for relevant trait impls that might apply to a given obligation by iterating through all applicable implementations.\n\nFor method-level trait resolution, `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/probe.rs` contains crucial logic:\n\n1. **`consider_candidates`** (line 1676): Filters and evaluates applicable method candidates, checking their applicability based on self type and obligations.\n\n2. **`collapse_candidates_to_trait_pick`** (line 2263): When multiple trait method candidates are applicable, this function collapses them to a single pick by ensuring all candidates come from the same trait.\n\n## Ambiguity Error Reporting\n\nWhen multiple applicable trait method candidates are found, ambiguity errors are reported through:\n\n1. **`compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/ambiguity.rs`**:\n   - **`maybe_report_ambiguity`** (line 160): Reports trait obligation ambiguity errors (E0283/E0284), handling cases where trait implementations cannot be uniquely determined.\n   - **`compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics`** (line 31): Collects all applicable trait implementations for diagnostic purposes, returning candidate sources for error messages.\n\n2. **`compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/suggest.rs`**: Handles method-level ambiguity errors (E0034 \"multiple applicable items in scope\") by reporting when multiple trait methods match the same call.\n\n3. **`compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/mod.rs`**: Defines the `MethodError::Ambiguity` variant (line 49), which stores a `Vec<CandidateSource>` representing the conflicting trait method candidates.\n\nThe flow chain is: candidate assembly → candidate filtering → ambiguity detection → error reporting. The ICE during trait method resolution typically occurs when the candidate collection or ambiguity detection phases encounter unexpected type states or when collapsing multiple candidates fails to properly handle edge cases in trait hierarchy resolution."
}

